sentences: Ta tegi suure tööga korda oma maja.
Me tegime koos nalja ja mängisime.
Ära tee nii! See on ohtlik.
context: The word 'tegid' is the past tense, third-person plural form of the verb 'tegema', which means 'to do' or 'to make'. It indicates an action that was completed by multiple subjects. In English, it’s commonly used to describe actions already finished and can often be translated as ‘did’, ‘made’ or ‘done’.
